translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 俺様の城が壊れるだろうがー！
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: My castle will be destroyed, won't it!

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: おはぎなら新しく作ってやるから！
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: If it's ohagi, I'll just make new ones for you!

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: アハハハ！　ざーんねん！
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Ahahaha! Too bad!

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: もう止められないよ！
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: You can't stop us anymore!

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ええ、そうね。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Yes, that's right.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 最後の一個のおはぎの価値は、
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The value of the very last ohagi is,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: それこそ値千金……普通のおはぎじゃもう……
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: truly priceless... ordinary ohagi just won't do anymore...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 私達を止めたければ、
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: If you want to stop us,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: チルディちゃんのおはぎでも持ってくることねー
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: you'd better bring Chilly-chan's ohagi.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ええっ！？　わたくし！？
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Eh!? Me!?

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: あー、そうそう。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Ah, that's right.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 菓子作りの腕がすごいという、
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Her skill in confectionery is amazing,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 彼女の作ったもんじゃないと、ちょっとねー
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: so if it's not something she made, it's just not the same.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: い、いやですわよ！？
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: N-no way!?!

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: なんで急に！
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Why all of a sudden!

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: あっ、この二人、最初からそのつもりで！
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Ah, those two were planning that from the start!

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: でも、彼女、菓子作りは嫌がってるから、
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: But she dislikes making sweets,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: きっと作ってもらえないわね
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: so I'm sure she won't make them for us.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: あー、このままじゃ、
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Ah, if this goes on like this,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 本当に殺し合いに発展しちゃうなー！
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: it will actually escalate into a fight to the death!

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: え、ええええ……？
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: E-ehhh...?

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: チルディ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Chilly

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: あ、ランスさま……
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Ah, Lord Rance...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 出来るだけ早くな
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Make it as quickly as you can.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: うっ、くうーーーーー……！
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Ugh, kuuuuuu...!

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: これはこれは……
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Well, well...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: おお……
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Oh...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 台所で、良い子にして待っていた二人の前に
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: In the kitchen, before the two who were behaving well waiting,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: どでんと、おはぎの山盛りが出された。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: a huge pile of ohagi was placed with a thud.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: もう二度と作りませんからね！
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: I won't make these ever again!

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: あらら、怒らせちゃった
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Oh dear, I made her angry.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 後で謝っておかないとね
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: We have to apologize later.
Mmm...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: それなんだけど、ごめんねぇ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: About that, I'm sorry.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: うん？
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Hmm?

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: あんな素っ頓狂な言葉でもなきゃ、
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: If I hadn't said something so outrageous,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 正直ちょっち止めらんなかった
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: to be honest, I wouldn't have been able to stop it at all.
Mmm...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 調子に乗りすぎたね
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: I got carried away, didn't I?

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 昔の血がちょっと疼いちゃった……
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The old blood stirred a bit...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: って言うね
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: that's what happened.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: へー、昔？
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Oh, in the past?

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 以前のあなたはどんな感じだったのかしら
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: I wonder what you were like before.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ひ・み・つ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: S-e-c-r-e-t.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ふふ、女の子は男で変わるものね
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Hehe, girls change because of the men in their lives.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ま、そーゆーこと
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Well, something like that.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: あたしの国じゃ……
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: In my country...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 今も大して変わらないけど、
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: it hasn't changed much even now,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 昔は妖怪の地位ってもっと低くってねー
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: but in the past, the status of youkai was much lower.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: だから、ま、戦わないと色々とひどかった
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: So, well, if we didn't fight, things were really bad.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 口調や性格こそ違わないけど、
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Although my tone and personality haven't changed,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: なんてーの？　スタンス？
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: how should I put it? My stance?

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 昔のあたしがビリビリー、なら
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: If old me was sparky and energetic,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 今はフワフワー、かねぇ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: now I'm more soft and fluffy, I suppose.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ふふ、愛されて幸せでいるだけの
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Hehe, just a sweet, loved, and happy girl...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 甘々とろとろーな女の子……
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: a super sweet and meltingly soft girl...

translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: I won't make these ever again!

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: あらら、怒らせちゃった
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Oh dear, I made her angry.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 後で謝っておかないとね
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: We have to apologize later.
Mmm...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: それなんだけど、ごめんねぇ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: About that, I'm sorry.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: うん？
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Hmm?

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: あんな素っ頓狂な言葉でもなきゃ、
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: If I hadn't said something so outrageous,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 正直ちょっち止めらんなかった
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: to be honest, I wouldn't have been able to stop it at all.
Mmm...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 調子に乗りすぎたね
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: I got carried away, didn't I?

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 昔の血がちょっと疼いちゃった……
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The old blood stirred a bit...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: って言うね
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: that's what happened.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: へー、昔？
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Oh, in the past?

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 以前のあなたはどんな感じだったのかしら
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: I wonder what you were like before.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ひ・み・つ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: S-e-c-r-e-t.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ふふ、女の子は男で変わるものね
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Hehe, girls change because of the men in their lives.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ま、そーゆーこと
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Well, something like that.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: あたしの国じゃ……
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: In my country...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 今も大して変わらないけど、
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: it hasn't changed much even now,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 昔は妖怪の地位ってもっと低くってねー
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: but in the past, the status of youkai was much lower.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: だから、ま、戦わないと色々とひどかった
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: So, well, if we didn't fight, things were really bad.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 口調や性格こそ違わないけど、
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Although my tone and personality haven't changed,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: なんてーの？　スタンス？
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: how should I put it? My stance?

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 昔のあたしがビリビリー、なら
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: If old me was sparky and energetic,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 今はフワフワー、かねぇ
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: now I'm more soft and fluffy, I suppose.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: ふふ、愛されて幸せでいるだけの
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Hehe, just a sweet, loved, and happy girl...

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 甘々とろとろーな女の子……
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: a super sweet and meltingly soft girl...
